      "options": {
        "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false },
        "content": "## Grafana Setup Instructions\n\n### 1. Install JSON API Plugin\n```\ngrafana-cli plugins install marcusolsson-json-datasource\n```\n\n### 2. Add Data Source\n- Go to **Configuration > Data Sources > Add data source**\n- Search for **JSON API**\n- Set URL to `http://localhost:8000` (or your FastAPI host)\n- Name it `Anomaly Detection API`\n- Click **Save & Test**\n\n### 3. Import This Dashboard\n- Go to **Dashboards > Import**\n- Upload this `dashboard.json` file\n- Select the `Anomaly Detection API` datasource when prompted\n\n### 4. Populate History\nRun a simulate call to populate the history panel:\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/simulate \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"sensor_id\":\"PUMP_01\",\"anomaly_type\":\"bearing_wear\",\"severity\":0.85,\"language\":\"both\"}'\n```\n\n### 5. Refresh\nSet dashboard refresh to `30s` or `1m` for live monitoring.\n\n### API Endpoints\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | /health | System health (model, PostgreSQL, ChromaDB) |\n| POST | /analyze | Full detection + RCA pipeline |\n| POST | /simulate | Inject synthetic anomaly + RCA (demo) |\n| GET | /history | Last 10 analyses (newest first) |",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Setup & Usage Guide",
      "type": "text"
